sputils.get_date", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "timestr", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Always parses the time to be in the UTC time zone; or returns\nthe current date (with UTC timezone specified)\n\n```\nparam\n\ntimestr\n\ntype\n\nstr or None\n\nreturn\n\ndatetime object with tzinfo=tzutc()\n```\n"]}, {"name": "adsputils.date2solrstamp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "t", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Received datetime object and returns it formatted the way that\nSOLR likes (variation on the ISO format).\n\n@param t: datetime object (we expect it to be in UTC)\n@return: string"]}, {"name": "adsputils.load_config", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "proj_home", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "extra_frames", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "app_name", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Loads configuration from config.py and also from local_config.py\n\n:param: proj_home - str, location of the home - we'll always try\n    to load config files from there. If the location is empty,\n    we'll inspect the caller and derive the location of its parent\n    folder.\n:param: extra_frames - int, number of frames to look back; default\n    is 2, which is good when the load_config() is called directly,\n    but when called from inside classes, we need to add extra more\n\n:return dictionary"]}, {"name": "adsputils.conf_update_from_env", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "app_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "conf", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "adsputils._replace_value", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "conf", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "new_value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "adsputils.load_module", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Loads module, first from config.py then from local_config.py\n\n:return dictionary"]}, {"name": "adsputils.setup_logging", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "name_", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "level", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "proj_home", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "attach_stdout", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Sets up generic logging to file with rotating files on disk\n\n```\nparam\n\nname: the name of the logfile (not the destination!)\n\nparam\n\nlevel: the level of the logging DEBUG, INFO, WARN\n\nparam\n\nproj_home: optional, starting dir in which we'll\ncheck for (and create) 'logs' folder and set the\nlogger there\n\nreturn\n\nlogging instance\n```\n"]}, {"name": "adsputils.from_object", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "from_obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "to_obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Updates the values from the given object. An object can be of one\nof the following two types:\n\nObjects are usually either modules or classes.\nJust the uppercase variables in that object are stored in the config.\n\n```\nparam obj\n\nan import name or object\n```\n"]}, {"name": "adsputils.overrides", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "interface_class", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["To be used as a decorator, it allows the explicit declaration you are\noverriding the method of class from the one it has inherited. It checks that\n the name you have used matches that in the parent class and returns an\n assertion error if not"]}, {"name": "adsputils.get_json_formatter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "use_color", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "logfmt", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "datefmt", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "adsputils.u2asc", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "input", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Converts/transliterates unicode characters to ASCII, using the unidecode package.\nFunctionality is similar to the legacy code in adspy.Unicode, but may treat some characters differently\n(e.g. umlauts). Standard unidecode package only handles Latin-based characters.\n\n```\nparam input\n\nstring to be transliterated. Can be either unicode or encoded in utf-8\n\nreturn output\n\ntransliterated string, in either unicode or encoded (to match input)\n```\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "adsputils.local_zone", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "adsputils.utc_zone", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "adsputils.TIMESTAMP_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "adsputils.ADSCelery", "bases": ["Celery"], "methods": [{"name": "adsputils.ADSCelery.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "app_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": [":param: app_name - string, name of the application (can be anything)\n:keyword: local_config - dict, configuration that should be applied\n    over the default config (that is loaded from config.py and local_config.py)"]}, {"name": "adsputils.ADSCelery._set_serializer", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["all of our workers should use 'adsmsg' serializer by default; 'json' is backup\nso we'll set the defaults here (local_config.py can still override them)"]}, {"name": "adsputils.ADSCelery.forward_message", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Class method that is replaced during initializiton with the real\nimplementation (IFF) the OUTPUT_TASKNAME and other OUTPUT_ parameters\nare specified.\n\nTo set in config:\n- For a single output destination:\n    - OUTPUT_CELERY_BROKER\n    - OUTPUT_TASKNAME\n    At call time:\n        self.forward_message(message)\n\n- For multiple output destinations:\n    - FORWARD_MSG_DICT = [{OUTPUT_PIPELINE: , OUTPUT_CELERY_BROKER: , OUTPUT_TASKNAME: }, ...]\n    where OUTPUT_PIPELINE is a string that will need to be specified in the call to forward_message as:\n        self.forward_message(message, pipeline=OUTPUT_PIPELINE)"]}, {"name": "adsputils.ADSCelery._get_callers_module", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "adsputils.ADSCelery.close_app", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Closes the app"]}, {"name": "adsputils.ADSCelery.session_scope", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Provides a transactional session - ie. the session for the\ncurrent thread/work of unit.\n\nUse as:\n\n    with session_scope() as session:\n        o = ModelObject(...)\n        session.add(o)"]}, {"name": "adsputils.ADSCelery.task", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**opts", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Our modification to the Celery.task."]}, {"name": "adsputils.ADSCelery.attempt_recovery", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "task", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "args", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "kwargs", "